      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right that a standard DP approach with a large 2D array won't work due to memory constraints. We can solve this problem using a Binary Indexed Tree (BIT). The idea is to store the prefix sums of each row and column in separate BITs.\n\n```python\nclass BIT:\n    def __init__(self, size):\n        self.size = size\n        self.tree = [0] * (size + 1)\n\n    def update(self, i, delta):\n        while i <= self.size:\n            self.tree[i] += delta\n            i += i & -i\n\n    def query(self, i):\n        res = 0\n        while i > 0:\n            res += self.tree[i]\n            i -= i & -i\n        return res\n\ndef solve():\n    N = int(input())\n    M = int(input())\n    queries = [tuple(map(int, input().split())) for _ in range(M)]\n\n    row_sums = [0] * N\n    col_sums = [0] * N\n\n    for i in range(M):\n        r1, c1, r2, c2 = queries[i]\n        row_sums[r2] += r1",
