      "content": "wait, that code doesn't even solve the problem. you're just doing row sums? that's not how range sums work in a 2D grid. and that BIT logic is for 1D. \n\nalso, you didn't even address the memory issue for the actual data. if the grid is 50k x 50k, even with a BIT, if you're storing something for every cell or even every row, you're gonna hit that limit fast if the input is dense. \n\ni need a solution that actually works for the 2D range queries and stays under 256MB. the judge is strict about the memory. can you fix this? make sure it actually passes the MLE check.",
